    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into small, bite-sized pieces, add to a heatproof bowl, cover the bowl with <strong>cling film </strong>and pierce a few holes in the top</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 5-7 min or until the sweet potato is fork-tender, once fork-tender, remove the cling film and allow to cool, discarding any water in the bowl</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brazilian-inspired-spicy-steak-with-charred-corn-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the sweet potato is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> to the pan and cook for 8-9 min or until charred \u2013 this is your <strong>charred corn</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brazilian-inspired-spicy-steak-with-charred-corn-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to a medium bowl with your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>oregano</strong>, 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>Brazilian-inspired marinade</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>rump</strong> <strong>steak[s] </strong>to the marinade and toss to coat \u2013 this is your <strong>marinated steak</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brazilian-inspired-spicy-steak-with-charred-corn-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Zest <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s] </strong>(try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter) and cut into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper, then chop roughly</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brazilian-inspired-spicy-steak-with-charred-corn-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the corn is charred, transfer it to the bowl with the cooked sweet potato and reserve the pan</p><p>Return the pan to a high heat and once very hot, add the<strong> marinated rump steak[s] </strong>to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 2-3 min on each side; for medium, cook for 3-4 min on each side, once cooked, remove to a clean board to rest</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brazilian-inspired-spicy-steak-with-charred-corn-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the steak is resting, add the <strong>chopped tomato </strong>and<strong> lettuce </strong>to the bowl with the sweet potato and charred corn</p><p>Add most of the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(save some for garnish), a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, a generous of pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and a squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong> and toss to combine \u2013 this is your <strong>charred corn salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brazilian-inspired-spicy-steak-with-charred-corn-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested steak</strong> finely on a clean board \u2013 this is your <strong>Brazilian-inspired spicy steak</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/brazilian-inspired-spicy-steak-with-charred-corn-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>charred corn salad</strong> drizzled with your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and a squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> sliced</strong> <strong>Brazilian-inspired spicy steak</strong>, <strong>reserved chopped coriander</strong> and <strong>lime zest</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
